Our birth doula service is designed to offer you comprehensive care and guidance during this transformative experience, and we are committed to helping you prepare for your upcoming birth and parenthood.

You will receive the following services:

  • Prenatal Visits -  3 visits for 3 hours each
  • Labor Support - rebozo, birth ball, breathing techniques, acupressure, birthroom ambiance, meals
  • Overnight Doula - 8 hours of support in anyway you need
  • Postpartum Visits - 3 visits for 3 hours each
  • Meals - light labor meals, healing postpartum meals, freezer stockpile
  • 24/7 On Call Support - beginning at 38 weeks
  • Virtual Consultations - via Zoom and SMS
  • Online Classes - FREE access to all online classes

Total Package Price: $3,000.00

Our birth package includes three prenatal visits where we will plan and discuss important topics before your estimated due date.

During these visits, we'll

  • Build our connection
  • Discuss your birth preferences
  • Create a Birth Plan
  • Practice relaxation techniques in our Labor Prep class
  • Talk about comfort measures and labor positions
  • Provide tips on laboring at home

These visits are designed to help you get ready for your baby, address any questions or concerns you may have, and ensure you feel prepared and confident for your upcoming birth experience.

Wondering what we'll cover? Check out our Planning Checklist filled with topics we can explore together.

Contact Us >

We are here for you 24/7 with on-call availability starting at 38 weeks gestation and continuing through your entire pregnancy, birth, and postpartum period.

You can count on us to be there whenever you need us, whether it's answering questions, providing guidance, or offering support during labor and beyond.

With our on-call availability, you can have peace of mind knowing that we are just a call or message away, ready to provide the support you need whenever you need it most.

After contacting your doula at onset of labor, we will be constantly available via phone, video call, and text to provide support as you labor before they meet you at home or at your preferred delivery location through the duration of labor.

Contact Us >

Your experienced doula will be by your side throughout your labor, providing continuous support, encouragement, and comfort, regardless of your chosen birth location (home, birthing center, or hospital). Our services include:

  • Rebozo Massage: Utilizing the traditional Mexican technique of using a shawl-like cloth, your doula will provide gentle and soothing movements to help ease tension and promote relaxation during labor.
  • Birthing Ball: Your doula will assist you in using a birthing ball, a large inflatable ball, as a tool for comfort, support, and optimal positioning during labor.
  • Breathing Techniques: Your doula will guide you through various breathing techniques to help you stay relaxed, focused, and manage pain during labor.
  • Complimentary Birth Photography and Video: As a special gift to you, your doula will capture precious moments of your labor and birth through photography and video, which will be provided to you on a flash drive to treasure for a lifetime.
  • Birth Room Ambiance: Your doula will create a calming and soothing environment in your birth room with a Himalayan salt lamp, essential oil diffuser, blood orange mist, and arnica massage oil to promote relaxation and comfort during labor.

With our comprehensive support through labor, you can feel confident and empowered during this transformative experience.

Contact Us >

Experience peace of mind knowing that our dedicated doula will be with you throughout the night, providing comprehensive support after your baby's birth. Our services include:

  • Overnight Support: Your doula will be by your side all night, providing compassionate care and assistance as you navigate the postpartum period.
  • Skin-to-Skin Bonding: Your doula will help facilitate skin-to-skin contact between you and your baby, promoting bonding and establishing breastfeeding, if desired.
  • Feeding Support: Your doula will offer guidance and assistance with breastfeeding or bottle-feeding, ensuring that you and your baby are comfortable and well-supported.

With our overnight doula care, you can rest assured knowing that you have a knowledgeable and caring professional by your side throughout the night, providing nurturing support for you and your newborn.

Contact Us >

Our postpartum doula services extend beyond the birth, providing essential support during the early weeks of parenthood. We offer:

  • In-Home Visits: Within the first two weeks postpartum, your doula will schedule visits to your home, providing emotional support, practical assistance, and answering any questions you may have about the birth experience or newborn care.
  • Emotional Support: Your doula is here to listen and provide a safe space for you to share your feelings, emotions, and thoughts about adjusting to life with a new baby, whether it's the good, the bad, or the tough stuff.
  • Resources and Tips on Infant Feeding: Your doula will provide valuable resources and tips on infant feeding, including breastfeeding, bottle-feeding, and introducing solids, to help you navigate this important aspect of newborn care.
  • Meal Planning and Grocery Lists: Your doula will help you plan meals and provide a grocery list to make your life a little easier during the postpartum period. We can also arrange contact-free drop-off of needed items through community support, a meal train, or assistance from friends and family.
  • Ongoing Postpartum Care: Your doula understands that postpartum care extends beyond the initial weeks with a newborn. We are committed to providing ongoing support to new parents, those with toddlers, or multiple children through simple acts of caring for the parent, while you care for your family.

Your postpartum visits are designed to meet you where you're at, from the comfort of your home, and provide comprehensive support to help you navigate the early weeks of parenthood with confidence and ease.

These meals are inspired by recipes from the amazing book The First Forty Days: The Essential Art of Nourishing the New Mother Amely Greeven, Heng Ou, and Marisa Belger. These women lay a foundation of recuperative eating to ensure bodily and mental healing for the birthing person that provides strength for the path of parenthood ahead.

settings.heading: For the Work - Light Labor Meal

settings.text:
During labor, nutrition and hydration are crucial. Your doula will provide you with a light labor meal to keep your energy levels up and support your body during this important time. The meal includes:

  • Bone Broth: Rich in essential nutrients and minerals, bone broth provides nourishment and hydration to support your body during labor.
  • Seaweed Soup: Packed with vitamins and minerals, seaweed soup is a nutrient-dense option that can help replenish your body during labor.
  • LaborAid Electrolyte Booster: LaborAid is a specially formulated electrolyte drink designed to provide hydration and replenish essential electrolytes during labor, helping to maintain your energy levels.
  • Frozen Fruit Pops: These refreshing and nutritious frozen fruit pops are a delicious way to stay hydrated and provide a natural source of vitamins and minerals during labor.

Our light labor meal is carefully selected to provide you with the nourishment and hydration you need to support your body during labor and help you feel energized throughout the process.

Contact Us >

Soup Options:

  • Classic Veggie
  • Chicken Noodle
  • Quinoa Lentil Greens
  • Squash & Red Lentils
  • Sausage Stew
  • C-Recovery Veggie
  • *Seaweed
  • *Fish Papaya & Peanut

Breakfast Congee and Porridge Options:

  • Oats & Chia
  • Sweet Potato Banana Walnut
  • Sweet Black Sesame
  • Farina Cranberry
  • Barley Blueberry Date

Granola Bag:

  • Assorted granola for quick and easy snacks

Bone Broths:

  • Lactation enhancement broth to support breastfeeding
  • Chicken or Beef

Soothing Tea and Steams:

  • Herbal teas and steams to promote postpartum healing and relaxation

Lactation Cookies:

  • Delicious cookies specifically formulated to support lactation and milk production

Our first week postpartum meals are thoughtfully designed to provide you with nourishing and delicious options to support your body's recovery and healing process during this special time.

Contact Us >

Preparing for the arrival of your new baby includes making sure you have nourishing meals on hand for yourself and your family. Your doula provides a freezer stockpile of homemade, nourishing meals that are perfect for during and after birth. Our freezer stockpile includes:

  • 5 homemade, nourishing and hearty freezer family meals to help you recover and replenish during and after birth
  • Easy to reheat options for convenience

Our freezer stockpile ensures that you have delicious and nutritious meals readily available during the postpartum period when your focus is on bonding with your new baby and recovering from childbirth. You can rest easy knowing that you and your family will be well-nourished during this special time.

A luxurious gift basket filled with our favorite postpartum goodies, a peri-bottle, date bites, a haaka, postpartum tea, and bone broth.

As part of our comprehensive doula package, you will receive a luxurious gift basket filled with our favorite postpartum goodies. This special gift is designed to support your postpartum recovery and includes:

  • Peri-bottle: An essential tool for gentle and effective postpartum care.
  • Date bites: A delicious and nutritious snack to help boost your energy and support lactation.
  • Haaka: A silicone breast pump that can help collect and store breast milk while nursing or pumping from the other side.
  • Postpartum tea: A soothing blend of herbs to support your body's healing process after birth.
  • Special Goodies: A mix of some of our favorite essentials for new mothers

These birth goodies are carefully curated to provide you with comfort, nourishment, and support during your postpartum journey. It's our way of showing you that we care about your well-being and want to help make your postpartum experience as smooth and enjoyable as possible.

Welcome to the pinnacle of personalized birth experiences - our Cliffrose Birth Package.
You're a conscious individual who appreciates the finer things in life. You value comprehensive support, detailed preparation, and superior care during your transformative journey towards parenthood.

The birthing journey can feel overwhelming, filled with questions and unknowns. How will you manage labor? Who will support you when you bring your baby home? How can you maintain your wellbeing during this monumental transition?

That's where the Cliffrose Birth Package steps in. Experience unparalleled support, from in-depth prenatal preparations to nurturing postpartum care. Our dedicated doulas, equipped with extensive tools and techniques, ensure a soothing environment that aligns with your birth preferences and nurtures your transition into parenthood.
